INSERT INTO `content_items` VALUES (24,26,21,'left',0,'Statistics','\r\n2/3 of refugees worldwide are displaced within their own country. \r\nThe countries with largest number of internally displaced people are Sudan, Iraq, and Colombia. \r\nMore than half of all refugees live in urban areas.\r\nThe Middle East is home to 4.7 million registered refugees.\r\n','<ul>\r\n<li><strong>2/3 of refugees</strong> worldwide are displaced within their own country. </li>\r\n<li>The countries with largest number of internally displaced people are <strong>Sudan, Iraq, and Colombia.</strong> </li>\r\n<li><strong>More than half </strong>of all refugees live in urban areas.</li>\r\n<li>The Middle East is home to <strong>4.7 million</strong> registered refugees<strong>.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>'),(121,140,21,'left',0,'Statistics','\r\nThe Indian subcontinent has nearly half of the world\'s hungry people.\r\nThe world\'s population will grow by more than 30% by 2050, resulting in 2.3 billion more mouths to feed.\r\nMalnutrition and hunger are responsible for 6 in 10 childhood deaths in developing countries.\r\nThere are more hungry people in the world than the combined populations of the United States, Canada, and the European Union.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','<ul>\r\n<li><strong>The Indian subcontinent</strong> has nearly half of the world\'s hungry people.</li>\r\n<li>The world\'s population <strong>will grow by more than 30% by 2050</strong>, resulting in 2.3 billion more mouths to feed.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Malnutrition and hunger</strong> are responsible for 6 in 10 childhood deaths in developing countries.</li>\r\n<li>There are <strong>more hungry people in the world</strong> than the combined populations of the United States, Canada, and the European Union.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(138,157,21,'left',0,'Statistics','\r\nOver 7% of persons living in the United States have been homeless at some point in their lives. \r\n45% of homeless adults have worked in the past 30 days. \r\n80,000 family households are homeless on a given night, 80 percent of them sheltered. \r\nFamilies are the fastest growing segment of the U.S. homeless population.\r\n','<ul>\r\n<li>Over <strong>7% of persons living in the United States</strong> have been homeless at some point in their lives. </li>\r\n<li><strong>45% of homeless </strong>adults have worked in the past 30 days. </li>\r\n<li><strong>80,000 family households</strong> are homeless on a given night, 80 percent of them sheltered. </li>\r\n<li>Families are the <strong>fastest growing segment</strong> of the U.S. homeless population.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(146,166,21,'left',0,'Statistics','  96 800x600     Normal 0     false false false  EN-US JA X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                          \r\n\r\n25 million people have died from the disease\r\nIn 2009, there was a global shortfall of $10 billion in funding for HIV/AIDS prevention and treatment\r\n10 billion condoms are needed every year to adequately prevent infections globally\r\nOnly 37% of those needing antiretroviral therapies in sub-Saharan Africa are receiving them\r\n','<p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <o:OfficeDocumentSettings> <o:PixelsPerInch>96</o:PixelsPerInch> <o:TargetScreenSize>800x600</o:TargetScreenSize> </o:OfficeDocumentSettings> </xml><![endif]--> <!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:View>Normal</w:View> <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom> <w:TrackMoves /> <w:TrackFormatting /> <w:PunctuationKerning /> <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas /> <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid> <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent> <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText> <w:DoNotPromoteQF /> <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther> <w:LidThemeAsian>JA</w:LidThemeAsian> <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript> <w:Compatibility> <w:BreakWrappedTables /> <w:SnapToGridInCell /> <w:WrapTextWithPunct 