" Priority=\"61\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Light List Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"62\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Light Grid Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"63\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Medium Shading 1 Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"64\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Medium Shading 2 Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"65\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Medium List 1 Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"66\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Medium List 2 Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"67\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Medium Grid 1 Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"68\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Medium Grid 2 Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"69\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Medium Grid 3 Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"70\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Dark List Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"71\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Colorful Shading Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"72\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Colorful List Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"73\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Colorful Grid Accent 6\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"19\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Subtle Emphasis\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"21\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Intense Emphasis\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"31\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Subtle Reference\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"32\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Intense Reference\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"33\" SemiHidden=\"false\"    UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Book Title\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"37\" Name=\"Bibliography\" /> <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"39\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"TOC Heading\" /> </w:LatentStyles> </xml><![endif]--> <!--[if gte mso 10]> <mce:style><!   /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable 	{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\"; 	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0; 	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0; 	mso-style-noshow:yes; 	mso-style-priority:99; 	mso-style-parent:\"\"; 	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt; 	mso-para-margin:0in; 	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt; 	mso-pagination:widow-orphan; 	font-size:10.0pt; 	font-family:\"Times New Roman\";} --> <!--[endif] --> <!--StartFragment--></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>3.57 million people</strong> die each year from water-related disease.</li>\r\n<li><strong>1 in 5</strong> child deaths is due to diarrhea.</li>\r\n<li><strong>90% of the 30,000 </strong>weekly deaths that occur from lack of clean water and sanitation are of children under five years of age.</li>\r\n<li>According to the United Nations, <strong>more people die worldwide</strong> from unsafe water than all forms of violence, including war.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(178,203,21,'left',0,'Statistics','\r\n75% of people living in developing countries live in rural areas.\r\nTwo thirds of Sub-Saharan Africa\'s population is employed in agriculture.\r\nWomen do up to 80% of the work on farms in developing countries.\r\n','<ul>\r\n<li><strong>75% of people</strong> living in developing countries live in rural areas.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Two thirds </strong>of Sub-Saharan Africa\'s population is employed in agriculture.</li>\r\n<li>Women do up to <strong>80% of the work</strong> on farms in developing countries.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(193,219,21,'left',0,'Statistics','\r\n63% of all households in the United States have a pet.\r\n5 to 7 million animals enter animal shelters nationwide every year.\r\n60% of dogs and 70% of cats in shelters are euthanized.\r\n10% of the animals received by shelters have been spayed or neutered.\r\nFive out of ten dogs and seven out of ten cats in shelters are euthanized due to not being adopted.    ﻿\r\n','<ul>\r\n<li>63% of all households in the United States have a pet.</li>\r\n<li>5 to 7 million animals enter animal shelters nationwide every year.</li>\r\n<li>60% of dogs and 70% of cats in shelters are euthanized.</li>\r\n<li>10% of the animals received by shelters have been spayed or neutered.</li>\r\n<li>Five out of ten dogs and seven out of ten cats in shelters are euthanized due to not being adopted.    ﻿</li>\r\n</ul>'),(195,221,21,'left',0,'Statistics','\r\n2/3 of refugees worldwide are displaced within their own country. \r\nThe countries with largest number of internally displaced people are Sudan, Iraq, and Colombia. \r\nMore than half of all refugees live in urban areas.\r\nThe Middle East is home to 4.7 million registered refugees.\r\n','<ul>\r\n<li><strong>2/3 of refugees</strong> worldwide are displaced within their own country. </li>\r\n<li>The countries with largest number of internally displaced people are <strong>Sudan, Iraq, and Colombia.</strong> </li>\r\n<li><strong>More than half </strong>of all refugees live in urban areas.</li>\r\n<li>The Middle East is home to <strong>4.7 million</strong> registered refugees<strong>.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>'),(1309,1545,27,'center',1,'What does KaBOOM! do?','KaBOOM! seeks to solve the lack of outdoor playtime for children that is often associated with problems such as childhood obesity, attention deficit and anxiety disorders, violence, and stunted development. According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, only 1 in 5 homes in the U.S. have parks within a half-mile. According to a KaBOOM! poll, 59% of children don\'t have access to a community playground. That number climbs to 69% in low-income communities, where children average 40 hours a week with electronic media and 30% of third graders have fewer than 15 minutes of recess a day.&nbsp;\r\nBy creating more playgrounds, KaBOOM! seeks to create healthier and smarter children, greener cities, better schools, and stronger neighborhoods.         ﻿','<p>KaBOOM! seeks to solve the lack of outdoor playtime for children that is often associated with problems such as childhood obesity, attention deficit and anxiety disorders, violence, and stunted development.<br /><br /> According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, only 1 in 5 homes in the U.S. have parks within a half-mile. According to a KaBOOM! poll, 59% of children don\'t have access to a community playground. That number climbs to 69% in low-income communities, where children average 40 hours a week with electronic media and 30% of third graders have fewer than 15 minutes of recess a day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>By creating more playgrounds, KaBOOM! seeks to create healthier and smarter children, greener cities, better schools, and stronger neighborhoods.         ﻿</p>'),(3122,4460,27,'center',0,'What does Malaria No More do?','Malaria No More is dedicated to ending malaria deaths in Africa by 2015. More than 2,000 people die from malaria in Africa each day. Children under five account for 85 percent of malaria deaths. Malaria costs Africa $12 billion annually, and 40 percent of its health resources are used to treat the disease. Their chief strategy for ending malaria deaths is the distribution of insecticide-treated mosquito bed nets, as well as local campaigns that educate Africans about the effectiveness of nets.         ﻿','<p>Malaria No More is dedicated to ending malaria deaths in Africa by 2015. More than 2,000 people die from malaria in Africa each day. Children under five account for 85 percent of malaria deaths. Malaria costs Africa $12 billion annually, and 40 percent of its health resources are used to treat the disease.<br /><br /> Their chief strategy for ending malaria deaths is the distribution of insecticide-treated mosquito bed nets, as well as local campaigns that educate Africans about the effectiveness of nets.         ﻿</p>'),(6935,5577,27,'center',0,'What does 350.org do?','Leading climatologists have demonstrated the need for atmospheric concentrations of CO2 to remain below 350 parts per million. Scientists have argued that the continued levels of CO2 above 350ppm will accelerate the already damaging effects of climate change. With the goal to lower carbon emissions and the concentration of CO2 in the atmosphere, 350.org was formed to advocate for efforts to end global warming.350.org believes that building a global grassrots movement will make leaders accountable to enacting long-term, large-scale change.&nbsp;&nbsp;         ﻿','<p>Leading climatologists have demonstrated the need for atmospheric concentrations of CO2 to remain below 350 parts per million. Scientists have argued that the continued levels of CO2 above 350ppm will accelerate the already damaging effects of climate change. With the goal to lower carbon emissions and the concentration of CO2 in the atmosphere, 350.org was formed to advocate for efforts to end global warming.<br /><br />350.org believes that building a global grassrots movement will make leaders accountable to enacting long-term, large-scale change.&nbsp;&nbsp;         ﻿</p>'),(8096,6448,27,'center',1,'What does Restavek Freedom Foundation do?','An estimated 300,000 Haitian children are enslaved as restaveks, children who have been sent by their parents to work for a host family as a domestic servant. Many of these children come from remote areas in Haiti where there are no schools or running water.&nbsp; While they are meant to work for host families in exchange for room and board and the chance to go to school, the reality is a modern form of child slavery where restaveks are often starved, beaten, forced to work inhumane hours, and kept from attaining an education.  Restavek Freedom Foundation works to improve the conditions for current restaveks and to advocate for the end of child slavery in Haiti.         ﻿','<p>An estimated 300,000 Haitian children are enslaved as restaveks, children who have been sent by their parents to work for a host family as a domestic servant. Many of these children come from remote areas in Haiti where there are no schools or running water.&nbsp; While they are meant to work for host families in exchange for room and board and the chance to go to school, the reality is a modern form of child slavery where restaveks are often starved, beaten, forced to work inhumane hours, and kept from attaining an education. <br /><br /> Restavek Freedom Foundation works to improve the conditions for current restaveks and to advocate for the end of child slavery in Haiti.         ﻿</p>'),(11271,1,21,'left',0,'Statistics','68,130 new cases new cases of melanoma in 20091 in 5 Americans will develop skin cancer in the course of their lifetime3,600,000 cases are diagnosed annually; skin cancer is the most common form of cancer in the US8,700 deaths from melanoma in 2009','68,130 new cases new cases of melanoma in 2009<br/>1 in 5 Americans will develop skin cancer in the course of their lifetime<br/>3,600,000 cases are diagnosed annually; skin cancer is the most common form of cancer in the US<br/>8,700 deaths from melanoma in 2009'),(11272,2,21,'left',0,'Statistics','370,000,000 indigenous people in Africa, the Americas, Asia, Europe and the Pacific4000 of the 6700 languages that are believed to exist today are from indigenous peoples20% of the Australian prisoner population is made up of Indigenous people, who make up less than 2 percent of the civilian population','370,000,0