oa farmers, whereas trading organizations and the chocolate industry receive about 70%<br/>7,500,000 producers and their families benefit from fair trade funded infrastructure, technical assistance and community development projects<br/>20% of consumers seem ready to pay more for fair trade products'),(11467,223,21,'left',0,'Statistics','1 in 2 children in the world live in poverty3,000,000,000 people live on less than $2.50 per day22,000 children die each day due to poverty','1 in 2 children in the world live in poverty<br/>3,000,000,000 people live on less than $2.50 per day<br/>22,000 children die each day due to poverty'),(11468,224,21,'left',0,'Statistics','50% of performing arts groups facilitate adult education programs and outreach77% of performing arts groups develop programs and performances for K-12 students7,000 performing arts organizations bring performances to more than 2 million audience-goers each week','50% of performing arts groups facilitate adult education programs and outreach<br/>77% of performing arts groups develop programs and performances for K-12 students<br/>7,000 performing arts organizations bring performances to more than 2 million audience-goers each week'),(11469,225,21,'left',0,'Statistics','75% of all net new jobs in the US are created by small businesses22,000,000 jobs in India are with small businesses51% of jobs in Korea are with small businesses','75% of all net new jobs in the US are created by small businesses<br/>22,000,000 jobs in India are with small businesses<br/>51% of jobs in Korea are with small businesses'),(11470,226,21,'left',0,'Statistics','1,165,351,327 movie tickets sold in the US in 2010360,000 people are employed in the film industry in the US$9,148,007,918 total 2010 box office gross in the US','1,165,351,327 movie tickets sold in the US in 2010<br/>360,000 people are employed in the film industry in the US<br/>$9,148,007,918 total 2010 box office gross in the US'),(11471,227,21,'left',0,'Statistics','45% sm