identifiable abortion provider, as a result, women must travel long distances to reach the nearest provider','','2011-02-07 15:29:10','2011-02-07 15:29:10'),(603,242,'In 1988, more than','125 countries in the world were polio-endemic. ','','2011-02-16 10:53:41','2011-02-16 10:53:41'),(604,242,'Today, only four ','countries are polio-endemic.','','2011-02-16 10:53:41','2011-02-16 10:53:41'),(605,242,'The remaining polio-endemic','countries are Afghanistan, India, Nigeria and Pakistan','','2011-02-16 10:53:41','2011-02-16 10:53:41'),(606,242,'One in 200 infections','leads to irreversible paralysis (usually in the legs)','','2011-02-16 10:53:41','2011-02-16 10:53:41');
