INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES (1,'Skin Cancer','skincancer','Skin cancer is the most common of all cancer types. It is categorized into two groups: melanoma and non-melanoma, which is the more common type. It is also less worrisome because, unlike melanoma, it rarely spreads. Common factors that increase the risk o','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(2,'Indigenous Peoples\' Rights','indigenouspeoplesrights','Indigenous peoples are among the most impoverished and marginalized people of the world. They consist of communities who trace historical continuity with societies endemic to their original territories prior to exposure to larger civilization. Land rights','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(3,'Abortion','abortion','Abortion is the termination of a pregnancy. It can occur naturally due to complications or be induced. Abortion has long been a contentious issue in American politics and society. Some people feel abortion murders the fetus while others feel as long as th','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(4,'Transitional Justice','transitionaljustice','Transitional justice is a response to widespread human rights violations. It provides recognition for victims and promotes possibilities for peace, reconciliation and democracy in societies transforming themselves after pervasive human rights abuse. It in','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(5,'Conflict Resolution','conflictresolution','Conflict Resolution refers to a set of practices used to mediate and end conflict. These practices can be derived from methods of mediation, negotiation, or diplomacy. The goal of Conflict Resolution is to end a specific conflict with the least amount of ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(6,'Leukemia','leukemia','Leukemia is cancer of the bone marrow and blood. Anyone can get leukemia, as it affects men and women of all ages.  The cause is unknown. Signs of acute leukemia may include easy bruising or bleeding, paleness or easy fatigue, recurrent minor infections o','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(7,'Catholic','catholic','','','',0,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(8,'Family Planning','familyplanning','Family planning refers to planning when to have children.  It involves disseminating information about the various forms of birth control, sex education, and sexually transmitted disease prevention and treatments. A major goal of family planning is to lim','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(9,'Obesity (U.S.)','obesity','Obesity rates in the United States are skyrocketing, especially among children, leading to an epidemic of diabetes and cardiovascular disease, and requiring a massive shift in both lifestyle habits and food industry practices.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-07-05 18:03:43','2011-08-16 10:52:40'),(10,'Organ Donation','organdonation','Organ donation involves removing tissue from a recently deceased person for the purposes of transplanting. Every day in the US, an average of 18 people die while awaiting organ transplants because of a shortage of donors. There are numerous legal, religio','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(11,'Prison Reform','prisonreform','Prison reform is the movement to improve the treatment of prisoners and the condition of correctional facilities with the goal of creating a more effective penal system. Rehabilitation for prisoners, including providing resources for education, work skill','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(12,'Stem Cell Research','stemcellresearch','Stem cell research involves research into how cells divide and replicate themselves (a property unique to stem cells), as well as how healthy cells replace damaged cells in living organisms.  Controversy over embryonic stem cell research revolves around t','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(13,'Marginalized People\'s Rights','marginalizedpeoplesrights','Marginalized people are those who are not considered part of the society in which they live. They may be excluded for reasons based on socioeconomic status, culture, religion or other reasons which force them to live on the fringes of society. Their margi','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(14,'Palliative Care','palliativecare','Palliative care is medical treatment that focuses on reducing the severity of symptoms that patients experience as a result of disease or illness.  The goal of palliative care is to make patients feel more comfortable, often by providing relief to symptom','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(15,'Pancreatic Cancer','pancreaticcancer','Pancreatic Cancer organizations advance research and support patients for those affected by the disease through community outreach and advocacy for a cure.  Pancreatic cancer is a leading cause of cancer death largely due to a lack of detection tools to d','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(16,'Alzheimer\'s Disease','alzheimersdisease','Alzheimer\'s disease is a neurological disorder that impairs memory, thinking and behavior.  Alzheimer’s develops slowly over a long period of time and worsens as the disease progresses.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(17,'Truth and Reconciliation','truthandreconciliation','Truth and reconciliation commissions seek to investigate and report on systematic or widespread human rights violations. They are often official state bodies that make recommendations to remedy such abuse and to prevent its recurrence. Typically, victims ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(18,'Suicide Prevention','suicideprevention','Suicide is preventable public health problem.  More than 90 percent of people who die by suicide exhibit signs of depression, substance abuse or other mental health illnesses. If properly treated with psychotherapy or appropriate medication, people who su','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(19,'Blindness','blindness','Blindness is the inability to see, usually caused by cataract, glaucoma, macular degeneration or uncorrected visual impairment.  Globally, about 85 percent of all visual impairment and 75 percent of blindness could be prevented or cured with improved eye ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(20,'Ecotourism','ecotourism','The main goals of ecotourism are to promote education and awareness of environmental issues, limit the negative ecological and cultural impacts of travel, help to finance conservation efforts, and improve the well-being of local people and environment.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(21,'Elder Care','eldercare','Elder care focuses on providing health services to elderly patients and meeting daily needs of senior citizens.  Advances in nutrition and medicine mean people are living longer than ever before. But with increased life expectancy comes social and public ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(22,'Aquariums','aquariums','Aquariums house aquatic life. The purpose behind most aquariums is to educate the public, provide centers for research and promote conservation ideals. However, some animal rights activists say that animals in aquariums suffer due to inadequate space and ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(23,'Female Genital Mutilation','femalegenitalmutilation','Female genital mutilation (FGM) involves procedures that intentionally alter or injure female genital organs for non-medical reasons. FGM is recognized internationally as a practice that violate basic human rights of women and girls and seriously compromi','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(24,'Primary Education','primaryeducation','Primary education is the first compulsory stage of education, a term more commonly used outside of the U.S.  The major goals of primary education include achieving basic literacy and competency in mathematics, history, science and other social sciences.  ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(25,'Asthma','asthma','Asthma is a chronic disease of the bronchial, the air passages leading to and from the lungs, causing difficulty breathing. There a variety of reasons that may explain the appearance of asthma in a person, but common causes are indoor or outdoor allergens','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(26,'Refugees','refugees','Over 40 million individuals worldwide are displaced or forced to flee from their homes to save their lives as a result of persecution or violent conflict.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-16 10:58:49'),(27,'Mental Health and Addiction','mentalhealthandaddiction','Mental health is the emotional and psychological well-being of an individual. Mental heal illnesses impact a person\'s thoughts, feelings, judgement and ability to function. Addiction is a chronic brain disease that causes compulsive behavior and substance','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(28,'Conditions','conditions','','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(29,'Diseases','diseases','','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(30,'Law Enforcement Reform','lawenforcementreform','During instances of systematic or widespread human rights violations, the military, police, judiciary and related state institutions are often instruments of repression and corruption.  As a country seeks transitional justice, the government seeks to tran','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(31,'Other','other','','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(32,'Reparations','reparations','Reparations are state-sponsored initiatives that help repair the material and moral damages of past abuse. They typically distribute a mix of material and symbolic benefits to victims, benefits which may include financial compensation and official apologi','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(33,'Respiratory Diseases','respiratorydiseases','Respiratory diseases include all diseases of the lungs, bronchial tubes, upper respiratory tract and other parts of the respiratory system.  They vary in severity from the common cold to life-threatening pneumonia.  Risk factors for respiratory diseases i','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(34,'Street Children','streetchildren','Street children are youth under the age of 18 who are either homeless or who work in the streets to support their impoverished families.  Deprived of an education and proper care, these children live an extremely difficult daily existence and are especial','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(35,'Heart Disease','heartdisease','Heart disease refers to conditions affecting the heart, such as coronary and congenital heart disease, heart attack and congestive heart failure. It is the leading cause of death for men and women in the U.S.  Preventative measures include avoiding smokin','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(36,'Clean Energy','cleanenergy','Clean Energy uses renewable sources like solar power, wind power, geothermal power, and plant matter to create energy. The goal of clean energy is to harness the earth\'s natural power in a way that creates minimal negative impact on the environment.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(37,'Free Elections','freeelections','Free elections mean that everyone has the right to vote in elections for public offices, and that every one\'s vote will be fairly counted. Free, democratic elections establish the legitimate authority of political leaders and promote government accountabi','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(38,'Principal Training','principaltraining','Principal training refers to how to prepare principals to effectively run schools.  As leaders of schools, principals are tasked with an enormous responsibility.  They must respond to student and teacher demands, ensure their schools meet testing standard','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(39,'Bullying','bullying','Bullying is intentional, aggressive behavior that involves an imbalance of power or strength. A bully may hit, punch, tease, name-call, intimidate or socially exclude his/her victim. Research indicates that children with disabilities or special needs may ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(40,'Diarrheal Diseases','diarrhealdiseases','Ingestion of bacteria, parasites or viruses causes diarrhea, which leads to rapid fluid loss, dehydration or dysentery. It is particularly dangerous in developing countries, where a scarcity of clean water, proper sanitation or adequate nutrition may prol','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(41,'Cholera','cholera','Cholera, an acute diarrheal disease, is an intestinal infection caused by the ingestion of contaminated food or water.  Left untreated, it can kill within hours.  Measures to control the outbreak of cholera include improving access to clean water and prop','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(42,'Religious Discrimination','religiousdiscrimination','Religious discrimination is the different treatment of individuals or groups based on their religious beliefs.  Despite acceptance that religious freedom is a fundamental human right, discrimination persists all over the world.  It may manifest in attitud','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(43,'buddhist','buddhist','','','',0,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(44,'Tropical Diseases','tropicaldiseases','Tropical diseases encompass all infectious diseases that occur predominantly in the tropics, which typically experience hot, humid weather conditions.  Examples of tropical diseases include malaria, cholera, leprosy and yellow fever.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(45,'Post Traumatic Stress Disorder','posttraumaticstressdisorder','Post Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) is an anxiety disorder that may develop following a terrifying event such as a violent personal assault, natural or human-caused disasters, accidents or military combat. People with PTSD have persistent frightening th','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(46,'Landmines','landmines','Landmines, weight-triggered explosive devices, are highly controversial weapons of war because of the indiscriminate harm they inflict on civilians, especially children, years after conflict has ended. They often remain hidden in forests, fields and roads','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(47,'Theater','theater','Theatre is a branch of the performing arts that entails the live performance of a drama or comedy, sometimes accompanied by music. Support for the theatre community consists largely of foundation grants that help maintain theatre facilities, financially a','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(48,'ADHD','adhd','Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder applies to children and adults who consistently display distracted, impulsive or hyperactive behaviors in an excessive way over a long period of time. To qualify as ADHD, the behaviors must create a real handicap i','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(49,'Food Aid','foodaid','Food aid is humanitarian assistance in the form of food supplies and programs to communities around the world that suffer from a shortage of food. It is a top priority for international health care organizations, as hunger is often the first emergency in ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(50,'Lung Cancer','lungcancer','More people die from lung cancer than any other type of cancer. Smoking cigarettes is the biggest risk factor.  In addition to searching for a cure, organizations are tackling lung cancer by promoting healthy living, running anti-smoking campaigns, and cr','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(51,'Stroke','stroke','A stroke occurs when blood supply to the brain is cut off due to a blood clot or burst blood vessel. Common symptoms include numbness of the face or one side of the body, confusion, difficulty seeing or speaking, loss of coordination and severe headaches.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(52,'Sex Education','sexeducation','Sex education may target any age or population, but is often discussed as it pertains to adolescents or other at-risk groups. Sex ed helps people acquire information, form attitudes and make informed decisions about sex, sexual identity, relationships and','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(53,'Victims of Torture','victimsoftorture','Torture is one of the most profound human rights abuses.  Rape, beatings, water boarding, burns, electric shocks, sleep deprivation and shaking are commonly used to break down victims. As horrendous as the physical wounds are, the psychological and emotio','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(54,'Prostate Cancer','prostatecancer','Prostrate cancer only affects men, growing in the prostrate gland over a long period of time. Some risk factors, like smoking, diet and exercise, can be controlled.  Others, like family history and age - the strongest risk factor for prostrate cancer - ca','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(55,'Privacy Rights','privacyrights','The concept of privacy rights has evolved from the protection of physical property to include medical, Internet, sexual, intellectual and political privacy, among other types.  Organizations dealing with privacy issues work to educate the public about the','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(56,'Depression','depression','Depression is a mental health disorder categorized by persistent feelings of sadness, anxiety, hopelessness, decreased energy and other signs.  A combination of genetic, biochemical, environmental and psychological factors cause depressive illnesses.  The','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(57,'Natural Disaster Prevention','naturaldisasterprevention','Natural disaster prevention efforts include the work of scientists, policy makers and the nonprofit community to limit the harm caused by natural disasters like earthquakes, floods, tornadoes and wildfires. Populations in developing countries are particul','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(58,'Native Americans\' Rights','nativeamericansrights','Native Americans\' rights issues include questions of tribal sovereignty, such as the protection of tribal lands and resources, protection of tribal rights to self-government, and provisional services necessary for tribal survival and advancement, as well ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(59,'Alternative to Incarceration','alternativetoincarceration','Juvenille detention for non-violent offenders has proved largely ineffective at curbing delinquency and reducing crime. States have responded by allowing alternatives to incarceration, like intensive counseling coupled with GED assistance and job training','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(60,'Colon Cancer','coloncancer','Colorectal cancers, or cancers that start in the colon or rectum, mostly begin as a polyp - a tissue growth that may or may not become cancer. Removing a polyp early may keep it from becoming cancer. For this reason, early detection is key to fighting col','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(61,'Prisoners\' Rights','prisonersrights','Organizations advocating for the rights of prisoners ensure that the treatment of prisoners complies with the Constitution, federal law and international human rights principles. Though denied liberty, prisoners have the right to medical treatment, religi','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(62,'Islamic','islamic','','','',0,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(63,'Right to Life','righttolife','The right to life mainly refers to the question of whether or not a person with a terminal illness should be allowed to end their life before death would otherwise occur. People who support the right to life believe that that ending a life prematurely sho','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(64,'Jewish','jewish','','','',0,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(65,'Ovarian Cancer','ovariancancer','Ovarian cancer only affects women and starts as a tumor in the ovary. There are 3 different types of tumors that can develop in the ovaries, depending on their originating cells.  Age is the biggest risk factor for women as most ovarian cancers happen aft','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(66,'Capital Punishment','capitalpunishment','Capital punishment, also known as the death penalty, is the execution of a person as punishment for an offense.  While execution has been used a form of punishment throughout history, only 58 countries currently have a death penalty.  More than two-thirds','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(67,'Freedom of the Press','freedomofthepress','Freedom of the press allows freedom of communication and expression through broadcast and electronic  media as well as published materials. It is a basic principle of democracy, as it fosters government  transparency, limits corruption and encourages a co','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(68,'Artist Residencies','artistresidencies','Artist-in-residency programs are places where visiting artists may stay to devote their attention to their art.  They vary in cost, but most are funded at least in part by government or organizational grants.  Artist residencies promote cross-cultural und','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(69,'Blood Donation','blooddonation','Blood donation helps saves lives by providing blood transfusions to patients with cancer, blood disorders and other medical needs.  It is also an integral part of emergency health care services administered during the most dire global situations, such as ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(70,'Architecture','architecture','Architecture and design informs the places where we live, work, learn, heal and gather. Designers, engineers, architects, and social entrepreneurs from all over the globe are devising cost-effective ways to increase access to food and water, energy, educa','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(71,'Brain Cancer','braincancer','Brain cancer affects children and adults differently, but in both groups, the cancer consists of tumors in the brain or spinal cord. Brain cancer organizations support patients and survivors through fundraising and advocacy work to promote early detection','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(72,'Labor Exploitation','laborexploitation','Labor exploitation includes the sexual exploitation of others, forced labour or services, slavery or practices similar to slavery, servitude and the removal of organs. Labor exploitation exists all over the world in shocking numbers.  Human rights organiz','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(73,'Genocide','genocide','Genocide is the deliberate destruction of a racial, ethnic, religious or national group through such acts as killing, inflicting serious harm and preventing births. It is largely considered to be the most severe crime against humanity.  Despite internatio','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(74,'Solar Power','solarpower','Solar power is a form of alternative energy that harnesses the energy produced by sunlight and converts it into electricity through photovoltaic technologies. Solar power is one source of alternative energy that environmental and clean energy organization','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(75,'Breast Cancer','breastcancer','Breast cancer organizations increase awareness of breast cancer through education, promoting early detection, as well as providing mammograms for those in need. They often fund and conduct research that helps us better understand, prevent, and cure breast','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(76,'Syringe Exchange','syringeexchange','Needle sharing is one way HIV and hepatitis are transmitted. Syringe exchange programs aim to reduce the number of people infected with HIV and other diseases via needle sharing by providing injection drug users with options to obtain sterile needles. Bec','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(77,'Child Marriage','childmarriage','Child marriage persists in many parts of the world gripped by poverty, where deeply rooted cultural beliefs and socioeconomic factors perpetuate the practice. As girls are often deprived of the same educational and economic opportunities as boys, families','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(78,'Cyberbullying','cyberbullying','Cyber-bullying occurs when a child or adolescent is tormented, threatened, harassed or otherwise targeted by another child or adolescent using the Internet, digital technologies or mobile phones.  If there is an adult involved in these behaviors, it is ca','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(79,'Patient Advocacy','patientadvocacy','Patient advocacy organizations serve as the liaisons between patients and their health care providers.  They work on behalf of patients to elevate their needs and ensure equal access to health care services.  Patient advocacy organizations often conduct p','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(80,'Smoking','smoking','Smoking is a risk factor for six of the eight leading causes of deaths in the world. Tobacco use is widespread globally, but it is an epidemic that is shifting towards the developing world, where 80 percent of tobacco-related deaths will occur within a fe','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(81,'Right to Die','righttodie','The right to die mainly refers to whether or not a person with a terminal illness should be allowed to end their life before death would otherwise occur. Supporters of this believe that people who are in great pain should have control over their own morta','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(82,'Zoos','zoos','Zoos are parks or institutions where animals are kept for exhibition to the public.  The purpose behind most zoos is to educate the public, provide centers for research and promote conservation ideals. However, some animal rights activists say that zoo an','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(83,'elementary education','elementaryeducation','Elementary education refers to the first compulsory stage of public education.  The major goals of elementary education include achieving basic literacy and competency in mathematics, history, science and other social sciences.  Access to elementary educa','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(84,'Entrepreneurship','entrepreneurship','Supporting and encouraging entrepreneurs creates economic opportunities and ultimately reduces poverty.  Entrepreneurs create opportunities for themselves as well as jobs for others. Providing training, increasing access to markets and capital, and advoca','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(85,'Children\'s Health','childrenshealth','Improving the health of children is top priority for international organizations fighting global poverty. 8.1 million children under five died in 2009, primarily from diarrhea, malaria, neonatal infection, and other treatable diseases. The vast majority o','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(86,'Sustainable Food','sustainablefood','The sustainable food movement aims to help people and businesses adopt environmentally-friendly habits by encouraging the use of locally-grown food, limiting the consumption of animal products, and promoting fair-trade and organic products, all of which b','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(87,'Community Development','communitydevelopment','Community development is the process of helping a community strengthen itself and reach its full potential.  Community development projects rely on the engagement of local people to improve housing, health services, education, farming, arts initiatives an','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(88,'Culture','culture','Culture is a term used to describe unique societal conditions that differ across various state, religious, ethnic, and political lines. Culture can include different forms of familial, ethical, artistic, and religious expression.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(89,'Veterinary Services','veterinaryservices','Veterinary services are those services related to veterinary medicine, which entails the diagnosis and treatment of injury and disease as well as the maintenance of health in animals.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(90,'Arab American','arabamerican','','','',0,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(91,'Sexually Transmitted Disease Prevention','stdprevention','Sexually transmitted disease prevention efforts center around raising awareness about how to protect yourself from contracting an STD, improving resources for testing and screening, removing the stigma attached to getting treatment, distributing contracep','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(92,'Libraries','libraries','Libraries house collections of books and reference materials for reading and lending.  They are more than important institutions for knowledge sharing and research.  Libraries are community centers and many provide Internet access - connecting remote comm','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(93,'Tuberculosis','tuberculosis','Tuberculosis, or TB, is an airborne bacterial disease that most commonly affects the lungs. It is highly contagious, though it is preventable and curable. One third of the world\'s population is infected with TB, which is the leading cause of death people ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(94,'Conflict Prevention','conflictprevention','Conflict prevention consists of the efforts of governments and international NGOs to stop the outbreak of violence before it starts. To accomplish this, they use tactics such as improving local capacities to mediate conflict, facilitating dialogues to bui','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(95,'Access to Healthcare','accesstohealthcare','Ideally, health care would be a basic right afforded to everyone. But a person\'s access to health care may depend on their socioeconomic status or location. International NGOs strive to improve access around the world by lowering the cost of life-saving d','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(96,'Art Museums','artmuseums','Art museums are institutions that specialize in the collection and study of objects of art, serving the public through education and engagement. Art museums serve to enhance our knowledge and appreciation of other cultures, celebrate past and present work','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(97,'Pakistan','pakistan','With 170 million people, Pakistan is the sixth most populous country in the world and the second most populous that declares Islam as the state religion.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(98,'Civil Rights','civilrights','Civil rights are the basic rights granted to citizens by a government, guaranteeing a set of fundamental freedoms protected by law. Civil rights promote equality in social, economic and political rights among people. Civil rights advocates work to end dis','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(99,'Pollution','pollution','Pollution is the contamination of land, water or the atmosphere resulting from human activity. Environmental and health organizations worry about pollution because it disrupts the balance of ecosystems, hindering plant, animal and human life. Air pollutio','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(100,'Government Spending Reform','governmentspendingreform','Government spending reform is the idea that governments need to spend money more wisely, so as to balance state budgets and avoid further debt. Fiscal mismanagement and deficit spending are common issues in governments throughout the world.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(101,'Fistula','fistula','Obstetric fistula is a hole in the birth canal caused by prolonged labour without medical intervention.  Most babies do not survive the birth, and mothers are left with chronic, leaking urine and/or fecal matter.  As a result, these women face humiliation','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(102,'Children with Special Needs','childrenwithspecialneeds','Children with special needs are young people with a physical or mental disability. The Individuals with Disabilities Education Act (IDEA) mandates that youth ages 3-21 with disabilities be given free and appropriate public education in the US. However, a ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(103,'Neighborhood Beautification','neighborhoodbeautification','Neighborhood beautification describes projects that aim to make communities cleaner and greener by planting trees, eliminating littering, preserving park and recreation spaces, and reducing pollution, among other local efforts.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(104,'Health Clinics','healthclinics','Health clinics may be permanent or temporary facilities that administer medical services to outpatients in need.  In places with limited hospital resources, clinics represent an important center for health, often providing emergency health care services i','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(105,'Horticulture','horticulture','Horticulture is the science of growing fruit, vegetables, flowers or plants. Horticulturalists play a role in the climate change debate by educating the public about the methods of food production and global patterns of food distribution.  They also parti','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(106,'Victims of Rape','victimsofrape','Rape is a serious crime that may also be a war crime or crime of genocide, depending on the nature of the assault. Most rape victims experience physical and mental health problems after their trauma, such as feelings of anxiety and guilt, phobias, substan','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(107,'Christian','christian','','','',0,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(108,'Cleft Lip and Palate','cleftlipandpalate','A cleft is a defect marked by an opening in the lip, roof of the mouth, or soft tissue in the back of the mouth. It can be treated by surgery, dental work, speech therapy and social work. But limited access to treatment in developing countries means milli','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(109,'Peace and Governance','peaceandgovernance','As a category, peace and governance refers to the continued effort to ensure governments around the world promote policies that benefit humans and the environment, are held accountable for their actions, and answer to the people they serve.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(110,'Child Abuse','childabuse','Child abuse involves the physical, emotional or sexual maltreatment or neglect of children under the age of 18 by a parent, caregiver or person in custodial role. Children who are abused are at higher risk for alcoholism, depression, drug abuse, eating di','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:06','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(111,'Human Rights','humanrights','','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(112,'Public Health','publichealth','The field of public health aims to safeguard communities from illness by improving access to medical care, sanitation systems and immunization, among other preventative measures. Global public health officials are primarily interested in research and trea','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(113,'population growth','populationgrowth','Improvements in science and medicine have led to higher birth rates and lower mortality rates for humans. But global population growth poses a threat to scarce natural resources. Environmental and public health organizations are challenged to derive solut','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(114,'Immigrants\' Rights','immigrantsrights','Immigrants\' rights groups in the U.S. work to ensure that immigrants are granted the civil liberties and fundamental rights guaranteed to all people by the Constitution. This includes freedom from discrimination and the right to due process. Organizations','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(115,'Public Policy','publicpolicy','Public policy refers to the decisions, laws, regulations and funding priorities of governments as they pertain to citizens.  Examples of public policies include health care spending, environmental regulations, military defense, immigration policy, tax ref','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(116,'Dance','dance','Dance is at once a universal and diverse form of artistic expression. Forms of dance include ballet, modern, salsa, hip hop, and ballroom.  Dance organizations aim to present their work to new audiences and to support the careers of dancers and choreograp','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(117,'Advocacy','advocacy','Advocacy involves the efforts to reform public policies or change public opinion about a political, social, economic or ecological issue. Organizations in this field give a voice to underrepresented or misrepresented citizen interests, with work typically','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(118,'Arts Education','artseducation','Supporters of arts education greatly value the inclusion of visual arts, music and dance in public schools. Advocates believe the arts to be a necessary component of childhood education, fostering creativity and diversity of expression amongst students. ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(119,'Infrastructure Development','infrastructuredevelopment','Many countries lack basic services like electricity, sanitation, and clean drinking water. Increasing access to these services by developing a country\'s infrastructure is a powerful way to break the cycle of poverty.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(120,'Arts and Culture','artsandculture','Arts and Culture form an integral part of every society. Across the globe people use visual arts, literary arts, story telling, weaving, singing, music, theatre, sculpture, and dance as a way of expressing their cultural heritage, mores, and history.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(121,'Volunteerism','volunteerism','Volunteers donate their time or energy to work for the benefit of others without financial compensation.  Volunteerism exists on the local, national and international level with one in four Americans volunteering.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(122,'Disease Prevention','diseaseprevention','Disease prevention deals with the efforts of governments and public health organizations to prevent the contraction of disease among a population.  Public health campaigns, medical research, statistical data collection, vaccinations and education tools he','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(123,'Nonprofit Management','nonprofitmanagement','Nonprofit management deals with running all aspects of a nonprofit organization in an efficient and effective manner.  Groups specializing in nonprofit management help organizations to achieve their goals through strategic planning, organizational develop','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(124,'Malnutrition','malnutrition','Malnutrition is the term applied to children and adults who lack proper nourishment or nutrients, usually due to food scarcity or abuse.  One in six global citizens are hungry or malnourished. Without proper nutrition, individuals are susceptible to a hos','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(125,'Public Spaces and Parks','publicspacesandparks','Public spaces and parks provide green spaces for people to enjoy nature or participate in athletic activities, among a host of other benefits to communities. They are especially necessary to create and preserve in urban centers, where nature access is mor','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(126,'History','history','History, from the ancient Greek word meaning investigation, is the study of the past.  Historians, institutions and museums provide a record of the past and a learning environment for everything from the history of people, geographies and economics to lan','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(127,'Medical Research','medicalresearch','Researchers study everything from disease causing pathogens to preventative measures and cures. Due to misaligned incentives among those that fund, conduct, commercialize and regulate medical research, the number of new treatments and cures for chronic an','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(128,'Freedom of Beliefs','freedomofbeliefs','The Universal Declaration of Human Rights, adopted by the UN General Assembly, maintains that everyone has the right to freedom of thought, conscience and religion, including the freedom to change one\'s religion or belief, and the freedom to manifest one’','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(129,'Secondary Education','secondaryeducation','Secondary education refers to the final stage of public education, usually following primary or elementary education.  It is an essential component of achieving social and economic goals, especially as demand increases for a sophisticated labor force.  Ho','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(130,'Health','health','Health refers to the physical, mental, and emotional well being of a person. People\'s health needs vary greatly. Health is affected by a variety of factors including age, sex, and socio-economic status.  ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(131,'Microenterprise','microenterprise','Microenterprises are typically small businesses with less than 5 employees. Particularly in the developing world, employment opportunties in the formal sector are limited and the barriers to starting a microenterprise are low. As a result, supporting micr','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(132,'Emergency Healthcare','emergencyhealthcare','Emergency health care involves delivering aid and medial assistance to people during health crises.  Emergency health care physicians and nurses treat malnutrition, disease and other pressing health needs around the world.  The need for emergency healthca','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(133,'Disease Control','diseasecontrol','Disease control deals with the response by medical and public health officials to the outbreak of disease.  It may include emergency health care services in the wake of disasters, public health campaigns, or other measures to treat the ill and stop the sp','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(134,'Religious Rights','religiousrights','Religious freedom is a fundamental human right. People have the right to worship according to their religious and cultural practices without fear of reprisal, violence, or intimidation. ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(135,'Physical Disabilities','physicaldisabilities','Physical disabilities impair the movement of limbs, hinder motor skills, or affect sensory or visual abilities. They may be congenital or develop as a result of injury, muscular dystrophy, multiple sclerosis, amputation or other conditions.  The proportio','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(136,'Land Rights','landrights','Land rights are a person\'s or entity’s claim to territory. They are of fundamental importance to the worlds indigenous peoples, since they constitute the basis of their economic livelihood and are the source of their spiritual and cultural identity.  Disp','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(137,'Digital Access','digitalaccess','Digital access refers to the ability of communities worldwide to effectively use Internet technologies. Digital access is crucial in a global economy for people to stay connected to news and information. The gap between populations with access to digital ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(138,'Hindu','hindu','','','',0,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(139,'Patient Navigation','patientnavigation','Patient navigation refers to services offered to patients, families and caregivers to help them overcome any health care system obstacles and accelerate processes to get patients appropriate treatment for their conditions in a timely manner.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(140,'Food Security','foodsecurity','An ongoing food crisis throughout the developing world has left nearly 1 billion people in a state of ongoing hunger, starvation, and food insecurity.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-16 10:58:14'),(141,'Reform Financial System','reformfinancialsystem','Reform in the financial system refers to the push for regulatory policies to control the banking system. The collapse of the housing bubble, which caused the recent global financial crisis, was fueled by a combination of easy credit conditions, predatory ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(142,'Music','music','Music is a form of art that uses the medium of sound to express ideas, emotions and experiences. It is a type of creative expression that can bridge cultural and lingual divisions thanks to its universal nature. Many believe the cultural significance of m','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(143,'Cancer','cancer','Cancer is the uncontrolled growth of abnormal cells in the body. There are more than 100 types, including cancer of the breast, skin, lung, colon, prostate and leukemia.  Cancer-related organizations provide support for patients and survivors, perform awa','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(144,'Workers\' Rights','workersrights','Workers\' rights organizations advocate on behalf of laborers to end discrimination in the workplace, abolish child labor, end forced labor, bolster unions and amend labor policies.  In today’s global economy, workers’ rights are increasingly an internatio','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(145,'Design','design','Architecture and design informs the places where we live, work, learn, heal and gather. Designers, engineers, architects, and social entrepreneurs from all over the globe are devising cost-effective ways to increase access to food and water, energy, educa','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(146,'Mentoring','mentoring','Mentoring a child or adolescent involves assisting with schoolwork, providing emotional support, engaging in physical activity or other activities associated with being a role model.  Coupled with formal education, mentoring can have a major impact on dis','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(147,'Literary Arts','literaryarts','Literary arts consist of various forms of creative writing, from fiction and non-fiction novels to short stories, poetry and prose. Literary arts organizations work to provide financial assistance and residency programs to writers as well as promote the s','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(148,'Environmental Justice','environmentaljustice','Environmental justice groups advocate for the fair treatment of all people with respect to environmental laws, regulations and policies. The primary goal of environmental justice is to ensure that everyone is protected from environmental and health hazard','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(149,'Schools','schools','Adequate resources and access to schools are crucial components for helping children achieve their potential and become productive members of society.  If schools lack clean water, teachers, study materials, social services or other essentials, the learni','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(150,'Stomach Cancer','stomachcancer','Stomach cancer tends to grow slowly over many years and spreads in different ways, sometimes affecting nearby organs, and other times entering lymph system and eventually the bloodstream. Risk factors include smoking, a family history of stomach cancer, c','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(151,'Children\'s Rights','childrensrights','Children\'s rights activists advocate on the behalf of children, ensuring that they have their basic needs met and are granted opportunities to reach their full potential. International organizations engaged in children’s rights seek to protect children fr','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(152,'Early Childhood Education','earlychildhoodeducation','Early childhood education is the education a child receives during the early stages of life, or between birth and age 8.  Early childhood education matters because it reaches children during their first few years of life when children develop critical soc','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(153,'Human Trafficking (U.S.)','humantrafficking','Human trafficking victims can be found across the U.S. The scope of human trafficking in the U.S. includes sexual and labor exploitation of U.S. citizens, foreign nationals, men, women, and minors.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-18 12:49:46'),(154,'Modern Slavery','modernslavery','Modern slavery is the illegal trade of human beings for prostitution, forced labor, or bonded labor, which is the most common form of modern slavery and involves work to repay a debt.  Governments and non-profit organizations combat these crimes by raisin','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(155,'Design for Social Change','designforsocialchange','Design for social change refers to the sector of design work that advances community development, corporate social responsibility or non-profit goals. Professionals in this field create sustainable products and services that cause limited harm on the envi','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(156,'Teenage Pregnancy','teenagepregnancy','Teen pregnancy is a social and public health problem because it is closely linked to issues like poverty, responsible fatherhood, education, child welfare, sexual health and risky behavior. Organizations that address teen pregnancy strive to educate adole','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(157,'Homelessness (U.S.)','homelessness','Stagnant wages, high unemployment, and an affordable housing shortage in the United States have led to historically high levels of homelessness throughout the country.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-16 11:02:40'),(158,'Nuclear Non-Proliferation','nuclearnonproliferation','Nuclear non-proliferation is the effort to limit the spread of nuclear weapons. 189 countries have signed the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty, including nuclear weapon states like the US, Russia, the UK, France and China. India, Pakistan, North Korea and','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(159,'Climate Change','climatechange','Human activities that result in carbon emissions are causing large-scale, permanent changes to the earth’s climate, resulting in multiple worldwide threats to humans, animals, and the environment.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-18 11:45:27'),(160,'Alternative Energy','alternativeenergy','Alternative energy sources- like wind, hydro and solar power- provide renewable options for energy, as opposed to nonrenewable fossil fuels (oil, gas and coal), which will eventually be depleted. Converting to alternative energy will reduce our reliance o','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(161,'Women\'s Health','womenshealth','Women\'s health covers much more than just pregnancy.  Health care for women focuses on preventative care and treatment for the biological, psychological and social issues that affect women. This includes diseases that affect only women, reproductive healt','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(162,'Environment','environment','Environmentalists seek to conserve species population, protect ecosystems, and ensure clean air and water.  Activities of environmental organizations include influencing public policy, cleaning up waterways, and researching environmentally-friendly energy','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(163,'Energy Conservation','energyconservation','Energy conservation matters because there are a limited amount of nonrenewable energy sources on Earth, the use of which pollutes the environment. Environmentalists therefore advocate for the conservation of our current supply of natural energy sources li','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(164,'Education (U.S.)','education','Cuts in public funding, challenges in teacher quality and retention, and falling graduation rates and achievement scores are leading to reduced future economic opportunity for young Americans.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-18 11:45:19'),(165,'Conservation','conservation','Conservationists value the beauty and diversity of the environment. Organizations in this field educate the public about the effects of human impact on the natural world, and help governments and communities develop innovative solutions to maintain a stab','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(166,'HIV/AIDS','hivaids','The global HIV/AIDS pandemic represents one of the greatest challenges to human health and is a leading cause of death in the world.  Since its discovery in the early 1980s, 25 million people have died from the disease.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-16 10:56:27'),(167,'Job Training','jobtraining','Job training prepares youth and adults to enter the workforce by giving them skills to improve employment prospects and succeed in new jobs.  Topics may range from computer or technical skills to resume-building workshops and career counseling.  Job train','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(168,'Education Reform','educationreform','Education reform is the movement to improve the quality of education available to all.  Topics in education reform include promoting polices that equalize access, permitting charter schools, providing training and support for teachers, graduating high sch','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(169,'At Risk Youth','atriskyouth','Young adults who appear at risk of not graduating from high school are considered at risk youth.  Specialized support, like access to housing, after school programs, and counseling, is often necessary to help them graduate.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(170,'Government Accountability','governmentaccountability','Government accountability is the notion that elected officials are held responsible for upholding public interest in their political decisions and process, especially as it pertains to government spending and funding for programs. It is a cornerstone of f','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(171,'Poverty','poverty','Poverty is defined by a lack of access to basic human needs like health care, clean water, food, housing, and education. People living in poverty lack the economic means to attain these services or goods.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(172,'Wildlife Preservation','wildlifepreservation','Wildlife preservation refers to the regulation of protection of wild animals and plants in an effort to maintain species population and ecosystems, often in defense of human impact.  Wildlife preservationists are primarily concerned with preventing endang','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(173,'LGBT Rights (U.S.)','lgbtrights','Lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender citizens throughout the United States experience prejudice and discrimination on a daily basis and live without many of the rights and legal protections afforded to heterosexuals.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-16 10:53:44'),(174,'Governance','governance','Governance refers to the process of governing a body of people. Governments are set up to deal with the day to day issues of governance; who is governing and who they are governing, how are policies disseminated, who\'s opinion is counted. Governance can r','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(175,'Peace','peace','Peace organizations seek to end all regional and global conflicts. They work to prevent conflicts, through and help communities recover from conflicts.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(176,'Women\'s Rights (Global)','womensrights','Women throughout the developing world suffer from ongoing discrimination, violence, and denial of access to education, economic opportunity, and political representation.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-16 10:54:55'),(177,'Nutrition','nutrition',' Access to proper nutrition helps fight off illness and disease and, for children, is vital to cognitive development and learning.  In the developing world, the primary area of concern is malnutrition while in the developed world it is obesity.  Proper nu','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(178,'Disaster Relief','disasterrelief','Natural disasters are a threat to all people throughout the world, but when they occur to poor and vulnerable populations in developing countries, the catastrophic effects are magnified, necessitating a collaborative and effective global response.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-16 11:03:22'),(179,'Hospitals','hospitals','Hospitals are institutions that provide medical, surgical or psychiatric care. They are relatively costly to establish and run, creating an unfair divide in access to care between rich and poor areas. Compared to their industrialized counterparts, develop','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(180,'Economic Empowerment','economicempowerment','Economic empowerment refers to programs that enable people to raise their recurring income and improve their standard of living. Interventions include training people for employment or starting a business, providing capital to entrepreneurs, helping peopl','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(181,'Maternal Health','maternalhealth','Maternal health refers to the health of women during pregnancy, childbirth and the postpartum period. Proper maternal health care promotes healthy women and children.  Tragically, the risk of a woman dying from a pregnancy-related cause during her lifetim','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(182,'Education Policy','educationpolicy','Education policy covers all legislation at the federal, state and local level regarding how school systems are run.  Key issues in education policy include funding for public education, resources for teachers, equal access to learning, national testing st','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(183,'Anti-Corruption','anticorruption','The mission of anti-corruption organizations is to achieve accountable, transparent and legitimate public and private sector institutions. Anti-corruption efforts involve empowering the public to feel actively engaged in their government, which in turn pr','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(184,'Innovative Technology','innovativetechnology','Innovative technologies include advancements in medicine, agriculture, the arts, governance, telecommunications and other fields that lower the cost of services, increase accessibility, promote sustainability and advance human development goals.  They cha','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(185,'Haiti','haiti','Haiti has a population of 9,648,924. Haiti is the poorest country in the Western Hemisphere with 80% of the population living under the poverty line and 54% in abject poverty. The life expectancy at birth is 29.93 years.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(186,'Animal Shelters','animalshelters','Animal shelters provide temporary housing and care to dogs, cats and other animals in need of adoption. They also rescue abused or neglected animals from the street and private homes. They are often supported by the work of volunteers.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-12 12:51:02'),(187,'Mental Health','mentalhealth','Mental health refers to the emotional and psychological well-being of an individual.  Mental heal illnesses impact a person\'s thoughts, feelings, judgement and ability to function.  Depression, bipolar disorder, anxiety disorders and eating disorders are ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(188,'Access to Education','accesstoeducation','Access to education refers to the opportunities afforded to children and young adults so that they may attend school or receive educational training.  Education organizations and professionals strive for policies that promote equal access to education reg','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(189,'Relief in Post-Conflict Areas','reliefinpostconflictareas','After a period of armed conflict, communities desperately need support to recover from the devastation caused by conflict. Relief in post-conflict areas includes ensuring access to food and clean drinking water, granting debt relief, rebuilding infrastruc','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(190,'Citizen Participation','citizenparticipation','Citizen participation is a cornerstone to democracy.  It refers to the notion that the public participates in government through elected representatives. Although the right to vote may be taken for granted in many developed countries, it is denied to peop','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(191,'Freedom of Speech','freedomofspeech','Freedom of speech is the freedom to speak openly without censorship. There are some legal limitations on this freedom, such as the prohibition of &#8220;hate speech,\" in many democracies. It is nonetheless a central tenet to functioning democracies.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(192,'Commercial Sexual Exploitation','commercialsexualexploitation','Commercial sexual exploitation of children is defined as both male and female children engaging in sexual activities for money, profit, or any other consideration due to coercion or influence by an adult. Many children are forced into the sex industry, wh','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(193,'Malaria','malaria','Malaria, a preventable and curable disease, is the fifth leading cause of death worldwide and poses a significant threat to both health and economic progress in Africa and throughout the developing world.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-07-05 18:03:45','2011-08-16 10:52:05'),(194,'Visual Arts','visualarts','The visual arts encompass painting, sculpture, photography and other forms of art that appeal to the visual sense. Visual arts organizations support artists and art programs through funding, residencies and advocacy.  They celebrate the diversity of visua','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(195,'India','india','With a population of 1.2 billion, India is the second most populous country in the world and the most populous democracy.  India boasts world-class, multinational corporations as well as the largest slum in Asia. India still struggles to provide basic ser','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(196,'Animal Welfare','animalwelfare','Animal welfare refers to the physical and psychological well-being of non-human animals. Animal welfare activists work to ensure that animals are treated with proper care and that adequate feeding and accommodation standards for animals are met. They advo','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(197,'Diabetes','diabetes','Diabetes is a chronic disease that occurs when the pancreas does not produce enough insulin (Type 1) or the body fails to effectively use the insulin it produces (Type 2).  Diabetes causes other health problems and increases risk of cardiovascular disease','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(198,'Sustainable Design','sustainabledesign','The field of sustainable design aims to create objects, the built environment and services that cause limited harm on the environment. To accomplish this, architects, designers and entrepreneurs consider the economic, social and ecological impacts of thei','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(199,'Arts Advocacy','artsadvocacy','Arts advocacy organizations promote appreciation for the arts through policy work and public awareness campaigns.  They often provide grants to artists and arts programs.  Believing that the arts are of incredible value, arts advocacy organizations strive','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(200,'Military Veterans','militaryveterans','A military veteran is a person who is serving or has served in the armed forces, and has direct exposure to acts of military conflict.  War veterans are generally treated with great respect and honor for their contribution to their country, however, too o','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(201,'Clean Drinking Water','cleandrinkingwater','Over 3 million people die each year of diseases stemming from contaminated water. Water-related illnesses kill more than 1 million children a year—more than HIV/AIDS, tuberculosis, and malaria combined.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-17 12:13:26'),(202,'Public Media','publicmedia',' Public media\'s mission is to serve the public good and engage audiences on a range of topics related to news, arts and culture.  Unlike other profit-driven media outlets, public media is funded largely through individual and foundation contributions, cor','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(203,'Sustainable Agriculture','sustainableagriculture','Sustainable agriculture can provide significant economic opportunity and self-sufficiency to small farmers and their families in the developing world, while simultaneously helping the environment.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-16 11:03:58'),(204,'Mobile Clinics','mobileclinics','Mobile health clinics provide medical and dental care to patients with who cannot access or cannot afford traditional health care systems. Doctors travel in portable vehicles equipped with medical devices to treat patients and train local employees. Mobil','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(205,'Environment and Animals','environmentandanimals','Animals exist in synergy with the environment. Animals rely on their ecosystem for food and shelter and the environment relies on animals to keep plant populations in balance and spread pollen and seeds for germination. ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-12 12:49:07'),(206,'Substance Abuse and Addiction','substanceabuseandaddiction','Substance abuse involves the harmful use of prescription or over-the-counter medications, illicit drugs, alcohol, or any other substance for mood-altering purposes.  Addiction is a chronic brain disease that causes compulsive behavior and substance abuse ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(207,'Foster Youth','fosteryouth','Foster youth are children and young adults who lack a permanent home and are temporarily placed in foster homes for care until they can be adopted or reunited with their biological families.  In part because of the instability of their environments, foste','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(208,'Global Warming','globalwarming','Global warming is the rise in the Earth\'s temperature due to an increase in greenhouse gas emissions, a result of burning fossil fuels like oil, gas and coal for energy. It’s an important global issue because the unnatural rise in temperature upsets the b','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(209,'Philanthropy','philanthropy','Philanthropy refers to the effort to improve human welfare through charitable aid or donations.  Philanthropic donations help to support a wide array of social and environmental causes such as education, arts initiatives, climate change, poverty relief an','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(210,'College Preparatory','collegepreparatory','College preparatory programs prepare students for college or university.  Programs and courses focus on the educational goal of ensuring teenagers graduate high school prepared for the challenges of university-level education.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(211,'Hunger','hunger','Hunger afflicts more than 800 million people around the world.  Chronic hunger leads to malnutrition, which contributes too frequently to death. The medical community has developed effective treatment for malnutrition.  However, access to treatment is ham','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(212,'Domestic Violence','domesticviolence','Domestic violence is the physical harm or emotional abuse exerted by one person in a relationship to control the other person. Instances of domestic violence occur across all socioeconomic levels and all types of relationships. It can cause physical injur','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(213,'Autism','autism','Autism is a developmental disorder that appears in the first three years of life and affects the brain\'s normal development of social and communication skills. Autism affects information processing in the brain by altering how nerve cells and their synaps','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(214,'Childhood Obesity','childhoodobesity','Childhood obesity poses a serious public health challenge for both developed and developing countries. It is mostly preventable, but has negative effects on the healthy development of children. Overweight and obese children are likely to stay obese into a','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(215,'Housing','housing','The Universal Declaration of Human Rights includes the right to housing. But factors such as population growth, migration to urban areas, lack of property rights, and insufficient financial and natural resources have caused widespread homelessness and hab','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(216,'Child Slavery','childslavery','Although the slave trade was abolished over 200 years ago, children are still enslaved all of the world, either sold by their families in depths of poverty, taken by human traffickers or abducted by other means and put to work. They endure physical labor,','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(217,'Museums','museums','There are more than 17,500 museums in the United States alone, serving the public through education and engagement. Museums are dedicated to the collection and study of art and artifacts, with institutions specializing in everything from natural history t','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(218,'Legal Assistance','legalassistance','Legal assistance organizations provide legal representation for low-income populations. Believing that no one should be denied justice due to poverty, these groups offer free attorney services, social workers and other forms of legal aid in criminal, civi','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(219,'Animal Protection (U.S.)','animalprotection','The use of animals by humans can lead to abuse and neglect, from agriculture and research testing to entertainment and domestic companionship.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-16 10:55:46'),(220,'Democracy','democracy','The most common characteristics of democracies include free elections, civil liberties, functioning government, political participation and political culture.  Although almost half of the world\'s countries are democratic states, many of these are consider','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(221,'Refugees\' Rights','refugeesrights','Over 40 million individuals worldwide are displaced or forced to flee from their homes to save their lives as a result of persecution or violent conflict.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-16 11:01:00'),(222,'Fair Trade','fairtrade','Fair trade is a market-based approach that aims to improve the conditions under which farmers and producers in developing countries enter into global trade with developed countries. The movement advocates for sustainable practices and a more equitable pri','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(223,'Poverty Alleviation','povertyalleviation','Approximately half the world, over 3 billion people, live on less than 2.50 dollars per day. Those working to alleviate poverty include small, community-based organizations as well as multinational organizations with budgets in the billions of dollars.  S','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(224,'Performing Arts','performingarts','The performing arts include theater, dance, music, opera, drama, performance art and spoken word.  Performing arts organizations serve the public through performance, education, and cultural exchange.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(225,'Small Business Support','smallbusinesssupport','Small businesses are key drivers of the global economy.  Providing training to small business owners, increasing access to markets and capital, and advocating for public policy that is friendly to small businesses can lead to sustainable economic growth.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(226,'Film','film','Film is a powerful medium used to entertain, educate or move audiences through a narrative experience.  Major film studios that once dominated the film industry now exist alongside a more recent batch of independent film companies.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(227,'Charter Schools','charterschools','Charter schools are public schools that operate independently of school boards, offering them greater independence in curriculum, teaching methods and philosophy.  Charter schools seek to increase access to quality education, especially in urban areas.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(228,'Artist Support','artistsupport','Artist support organizations help artists to fulfill personal and professional goals while encouraging broader participation and appreciation for the arts in society. Organizations facilitate artistic creation through grants, commissions and financial and','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(229,'Early Childhood Health','earlychildhoodhealth','Early childhood health care is critical to ensure a successful start in life.  It provides children with preventative care, immunization and proper nutrition during their first few years of life, as well as education and services for mothers.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(230,'Criminal Justice','criminaljustice','Criminal justice is the system that protects public safety, deters crime, and sanctions those who violate laws.  Organizations working in this area seek to help government make the system more effective, fair, and humane for all.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(231,'Reproductive Rights','reproductiverights','Reproductive rights consist of the freedom to make decisions regarding family planning, particularly the use of various forms of contraception and abortion. Some nations refuse to recognize the existence of reproductive rights, while others have codified ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(232,'After School Programs','afterschoolprograms','Afterschool programs offer classes and activities outside of the normal school day in public education.  They may be academic, athletic or artistic in nature.  Supporters of afterschool programs believe they provide a necessary outlet for students, especi','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(233,'Water','water','Access to clean water is a necessity for human life, yet it is shockingly scarce for much of the world\'s population. Environmental groups strive both to protect our oceans and aquatic life, as well as to improve water access and quality.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-12 12:46:35'),(234,'Teacher Training','teachertraining','Teacher training refers to how to prepare teachers so that they can better educate their students.  The topic includes measures to support teachers, improve their status and encourage their professional development, as well as training courses to teach th','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(235,'Sports','sports','Sports organizations strive to use athletic activities as a method to promote social responsibility and wellness, particularly in under-served communities. By using sports like basketball, baseball, soccer and martial arts, groups in this field hope to en','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(236,'Land Conservation','landconservation','Land conservation refers to the efforts of organizations and governments to protect land from over-development, deforestation, pollution and climate change. With the global population expected to increase from 6 to at least 9 billion by 2050, forests, gra','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(237,'Microfinance','microfinance','Microfinance organizations provide small loans and savings accounts to low-income individuals who lack access to typical banking services. The microfinance movement aims to lift people out of poverty by providing them with access to capital to start a bus','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(238,'Air Quality','airquality','Environmentalists and public health officials are concerned with air quality since poor air quality can have detrimental effects. Regulations control the amount of lead, carbon monoxide and pollutants emitted by cars, factories and power plants. Children,','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(239,'Girls Education','girlseducation','Gender difference represents a major barrier preventing equal access to education. Particularly in developing countries, boys are sent to school while many girls are denied this basic right and are kept at home for domestic work. International organizatio','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-04 11:02:07','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(240,'Pro-life','prolife','Pro-life is a phrase used to describe an ideological stance against elective abortion, and a support for restrictive laws and prohibition. Pro-lifers believe that life begins at conception, they support alternatives like adoption.','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-07 15:26:15','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(241,'Pro-Choice','prochoice','Pro-choice is the ideology that a woman has the right to control what happens to her body by continuing or terminating a pregnancy. Pro-choicers focus on issues of access, empowerment, civil rights, and women’s rights. ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-07 15:29:10','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(242,'Polio','polio','Polio is a viral disease that attacks the nervous system and is highly contagious. It is spread by ingesting contaminated food or water. Polio has decreased significantly since 1950, when a vaccine was devised. ','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-02-16 10:53:41','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(243,'Egypt','egypt','','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-03-02 17:02:52','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(244,'Down Syndrome','downsyndrome','','','',1,0,NULL,'2011-04-07 10:44:51','2011-08-11 17:49:35'),(245,'Women\'s Rights (U.S.)','womensrightsus','Despite tremendous strides in achieving legal protections and equal rights, women in the United States face continued barriers and challenges in terms of economic opportunity, reproductive rights, and safety.','','',1,1,NULL,'2011-08-11 13:00:32','2011-08-16 10:55:14');
